  <description type="morphology">Shrubs, sprawling, with numerous branches, usually at obtuse angles. Stem segments
        green to dark green, 8–20(–31) cm; tubercles salient, moderately broad, 1.5–2.5 cm. Spines
        14–18(–23) per areole, yellow to deep red-brown, aging gray, not baggy sheathed; major
        abaxial spines usually deflexed, spreading. Flowers: inner tepals yellow, bronze, or brick
        red. Fruits spiny; areoles 14–22(–26). 2n = 22.</description>
